title: Dublin Airport resumes flights after fire on roof of a hangarTravelandtourworld.com
text:
Dublin Airport resumes flights after fire on roof of a hangar Published on : Wednesday, August 26, 2015
Dublin Airport has resumed flights after a fire on the roof of a hangar was brought under control. In an untoward incident, the roof of a hangar in Dublin Airport caught fire and alarm was raised at about 07:15 local time.
Four fire brigade service vehicles were immediately dispatched to the scene of action to douse the fire.
Meanwhile, the airport suspended flights for 90 minutes. A number of flights were diverted to Belfast City and Shannon airports.
The Dublin Airport Authority regretted any inconvenience caused to passengers.
The fire was in a restricted area, separate from the passenger facilities and there are no reports of any injuries and the aircraft in the hangar has not been affected, confirmed the airport authority.
